<h2>GuideSpark React UI Component Engine</h2>

<hr>

<h3>Overview</h3>
<blockquote>
  <p>This is a rails engine to help you easily build bootstrap style UI
    components with
    <%= link_to 'React', 'https://facebook.github.io/react/', target: '_blank' %>.
  </p>
</blockquote>

<br>

<h3>Requirement</h3>
<blockquote>
  <ul>
    <li>rails 4.2.0+</li>
    <li>react-rails 1.6.0+ (react.js and react-dom.js are included in this
      gem)
    </li>
    <li>bootstrap 3.3.0+</li>
    <li>jQuery 1.7.0+ (required if need bootstrap jQuery plugins)</li>
    <li>font-awesome 4.5.0+</li>
  </ul>
</blockquote>

<br>

<h3>Installation</h3>

<p>Add this line to your application's Gemfile:</p>
<pre>
  gem 'gs_react_ui'
</pre>
<p>And then execute:</p>
<pre>
  $ bundle
</pre>
<p>Or install it yourself as:</p>
<pre>
  gem install gs_react_ui
</pre>

<blockquote class='text-warning'>
  bootstrap and font-awesome need installing independently.
</blockquote>

<p>In application.js, add the following lines:</p>
<pre>
  //= require react/react
  //= require react/react-dom
  //= require react_ujs
  //= require gs_react_ui/components
  * //= require bootstrap (if needed) *
</pre>

<p>In application.css, add the following lines:</p>
<pre>
  *= require bootstrap
  *= require font-awesome
  *= require gs_react_ui/application
</pre>